<div class="doc_title">Quick Tour</div>

<p><strong>WP Data Access helps you to</strong></p>
<ul class="doc_list">
  <li>Manage your WordPress data and database</li>
  <li>Building WordPress data apps that run in the WordPress dashboard</li>
  <li>Publish your WordPress data on your website</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Manage your WordPress data and database</strong></p>
<p class="doc_margin">Use the Data Explorer main page to perform database administration tasks from your WordPress dashboard on tables and indexes like create, drop, truncate, rename, copy, export and import. The Data Explorer main page can be reached from the Data Explorer menu item.</p>
<p class="doc_margin">Use Data Explorer table pages to perform data adminstration tasks from your WordPress dashboard on tables and indexes. Query tables and indexes using intuitive list tables and perform insert, update and delete operations through data entry forms generated on the fly. Data Explorer table page can be reached through the Data Explorer main page by clickin on the Explore link of a specific table or view.</p>

<p><strong>Building WordPress data apps that run in the WordPress dashboard</strong></p>
<p class="doc_margin">Use Data Projects to build WordPress data apps that run in the WordPress dashboard. Create your own WordPress dashboard menu and add static pages or pages which handle your own database tables to it. Data Projects offers support to build standard CRUD forms as well as parent-child forms with just a few mouse clicks.</p>

<p><strong>Publish your WordPress data on your website</strong></p>
<p class="doc_margin">Publish data on your website using shortcodes. WP Data Access uses jQuery Datatables to publish your data (supports searching, pagination, sorting).</p>

